{
  "texts": [
    "PEFT methods either update a subset of the model's parameters or introduce lightweight external modules to enhance efficiency [91].",
    "These techniques have been widely adopted in LLM applications and include:-Adapters: Trainable modules inserted into the model's architecture [43,92].",
    "-Soft Prompts: Task-specific embeddings added to the input sequence [93].-Selective Updates: Methods like BitFit [94], which update only specific parameters, such as bias terms, while freezing the rest of the model.Among PEFT techniques, Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRa) [44] stands out as a particularly effective method.",
    "LoRa and Its VariantsLoRa employs low-rank decomposition to parameterize weight updates.",
    "For a pretrained weight matrix W 0 ∈ R d×k, the weight update is defined as:W 0 + ∆W = W 0 + BA,(3)where B ∈ R d×r and A ∈ R r×k, and r ≪ min(d, k)."
  ]
}